        <detaileddescription>
<para>load scene from MISON file <linebreak/>
JSON file with array named &quot;Objects&quot; or root array: <linebreak/>
element fields:<linebreak/>
 &quot;Filename&quot; : required full path to file for loading object &quot;XF&quot;: optional xf for loaded object &quot;Name&quot;: optional name for loaded object Generated from function <computeroutput>MR::fromSceneMison</computeroutput>. Parameter <computeroutput>path</computeroutput> is a UTF-8 encoded filesystem path. Parameter <computeroutput>callback</computeroutput> is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>callback</computeroutput> has a default argument: <computeroutput>{}</computeroutput>, pass a null pointer to use it. Never returns null. Returns an instance allocated on the heap! Must call <computeroutput>MR_expected_MR_LoadedObjectT_std_string_Destroy()</computeroutput> to free it when you&apos;re done using it. </para>
